Config(address,uint256).details: Account has set a new swap configuration.

Swap(address,uint256,uint256,uint256,uin.details: A swap operation has been completed.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract by setting the list of available DEXs as well as the contract owner.

fetchBaseGasPrice().details: Fetch and store base gas price from VeChain Params contract. Anybody should be able to call this function.

saveConfig(uint256).details: Associate reserveBalance to the caller. Enforce reserveBalance to be non zero so that when the `swap` method gets called we can verify that the config has been initilized.

setAdmin(address).details: Set a new admin account. The caller must have owner role.

setFeeMultiplier(uint8).details: Set a new protocol feeMultiplier. The caller must have owner role. The supplied value must be between 0 and 30 (0% and 0.3% fee respectively).

withdrawFees().details: Withdraw fees accrued by the protocol. The caller must have owner role. Accrued fees include both protocol and transaction fees. Use the `Transfer` event emitted by the Energy contract to track this method call.

MAX_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.details: Maximum VTHO amount that can be withdrawn in one trade. The aim is to prevent sandwich attacks.

SWAP_GAS.details: Estimated gas cost for running the swap function with an upper bound of 0xfffffffffffffffffff for the withdrawAmount input.

admin.details: Protocol admin. The admin is the only role with access to swap function.

baseGasPrice.details: Base gas price fetched from Params VeChain contract.

feeMultiplier.details: Multiplier used to calculate protocol fee based on the following formula: uint256 protocolFee = amount * feeMultiplier / 10_000. For instance, if feeMultiplier equals 30, it means we are applying a 0.3 % fee to the amount being swapped.

owner.details: Protocol owner. The owner is the only role with access to the setFeeMultiplier, setAdmin and withdrawFees functions.

params.details: Interface to interact with the Params contract.

reserves.details: Dictionary matching account address to reserveBalance.

routers.details: Interface to interact with the UniswapV2 routers.

vtho.details: Interface to interact with the Energy (VTHO) contract.

devdoc.title: Params stores the governance params of VeChain thor. The params can be set by the executor, a contract that is authorized to modify governance params by a voting Committee. You can check these params at source file: https://github.com/vechain/thor/blob/master/thor/params.go.

@title Params stores the governance params of VeChain thor.
